import pyautogui
import time
import uiautomation as auto

def open_whatsapp():
    try:
        # Press Windows key to open Start menu
        pyautogui.press('win')
        time.sleep(0.5)
        # Type WhatsApp
        pyautogui.write('WhatsApp', interval=0.1)
        time.sleep(0.5)
        # Press Enter to launch
        pyautogui.press('enter')
        time.sleep(2)
        # Verify WhatsApp window appears
        whatsapp = auto.WindowControl(searchDepth=1, ClassName='Chrome_WidgetWin_1')
        if whatsapp.Exists():
            print("EXECUTION_SUCCESS")
        else:
            print("FAILED: WhatsApp window not found")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"FAILED: {e}")

open_whatsapp()
